block content

  +state('Massachusetts', '/assets/images/flag-massachusetts.svg', 'The Bay State', 'February 6, 1788', 'border')

  .intro
    p The Massachusetts flag was the first state (commonwealth) flag to feature a plain white field and, for about 50 years, was a rare two-sided design.
    p The flag (and the seal) have received criticism for its depiction of a Native American man beneath a faceless arm weilding a broadsword. There is still pressure for Massachusetts to make changes to these symbols.
    p The current flag was officially adopted July 3, 1971.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The flag features a field of white upon which the state coat of arms, in blue and gold, is placed at the center.
    .visual.flag
      img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-massachusetts.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-massachusetts-icon-algonquin.svg')
          h4 Algonquin
          p The Algonquin man represents the Native people who taught the pilgrims how to survive in Massachusetts.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-massachusetts-icon-arrow.svg')
          h4 Arrow
          p The arrow in the Algonquin man’s hand is pointed down, meant to symbolize peace.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-massachusetts-icon-star.svg')
          h4 Star
          p The star represents Massachusetts as one of the original 13 colonies.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-massachusetts-icon-broadsword.svg')
          h4 Arm with broadsword
          p A visual representation of the state motto: “By the Sword We Seek Peace, But Peace Only Under Liberty.”

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Coat of Arms
      p The Massachusetts coat of arms was adopted in 1775. Inscribed in Latin on the ribbon are the words “Ense petit placidam sub libertate quietem” which translate to “By the Sword We Seek Peace, But Peace Only Under Liberty.”
      p Despite the claim that the broadsword references the state’s motto, the imagery of a Native American beneath an arm weilding a sword has caused a great deal of pain, reminding many of the violence inflicted on Native Americans.
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/coat-of-arms-massachusetts.jpg')

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p The blue of the flag represents the Blue Hills of Canton. The five-pointed star is white, unlike the state seal where it appears silver.
    .visual.colors.primary
      .color
        .sample(class='white')
        .name White
        .hex #ffffff
      .color
        .sample(class='blue')
        .name Blue
        .hex #1f2c5c
      .color
        .sample(class='gold')
        .name Gold
        .hex #e6a300

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p The Massachusetts flag is usually produced with a proportion of 3:5.
      p If resized, it will maintain these proportions.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-massachusetts-dimensions.svg')

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Previous iteration
      p Before 1971, the Massachusetts flag had a different design on its reverse. It featured the blue shield with a pine tree.
      p With the importance of timber in the region, the pine tree became a symbol of New England. After the #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pine_Tree_Riot') Pine Tree Riot] in 1772, it persisted as an emblem for resistance and independence.
    .visual.flag
      img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-massachusetts-reverse.svg')

